<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-731-847  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 731 847.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Dec 20 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New CD-ROM publishing service. (R.R. Donnelley Co.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mallory, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   R.R. Donnelley and Sons Co. (Publishing).andO;Topic:     CD-ROMPublishing IndustryProduct Development.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW CD-ROM PUBLISHING SERVICE 12/20/90 CHICAGO, ILLINOIS, U.S.A., 1990 DEC 20(NB) -- R.R.andP;  Donnelley Co has announced availability of a new publishingservice using CD-ROM technology which provides updates to complex documentssuch as parts catalogs, inventory listings, and engineering designspecifications.andP;  Listings can include text, charts, graphs, schematics andphotographs formatted to read and look exactly like those in printed manualsand catalogs.andM;On a regular basis as desired by the customer, R.R.andP;  Donnelley and Sonsproduces updated documents and distributes them to their clients offices.andO;The company sees an emerging market in companies that publish extensivecatalogs for such items as office supplies, electronics components, medicalinstrumentation, tools, and parts.andM;Donnelley's initial customer is Intel Corporation, whose 90 worldwide salesoffices will receive monthly updates to the 15 volumes of specificationsconsisting of more than 17,000 pages.andP;  More than half of these requirerevision each year.andP;  Each office will receive an updated CD-ROM diskcontaining all the product information currently found in Intel's catalogs,along with notes on any revisions made to each product entry.andM;Intel anticipates that the turn-around time for customer requests will bedrastically reduced over the time associated with paper document management.andM;CD-ROM disks are a relatively new technology in the computer field.andO;Information is stored on the disk and can be read but not altered, making itmore reliable than other storage media such as floppy or hard drives.andM;R.R.andP;  Donnelley and Sons Co prints catalogs, newspaper advertising inserts,magazines, books, directories, computer documentation and financial printing.andM;(Jim Mallory/19901219)</TEXT></DOC>